The early popularity of Virgil has secured the transmission of his works to us in a larger number of manuscripts than those of almost any other ancient writer. The history of the text is too long for this place, but it may be found well set forth in Ribbeck's Prolegomena to Virgil. The oldest and most important MSS. are seven, written in capitaIS‚
